# lowcode-bpmn

Go BPMN 2.0 engine microservice. JSON + BPMN XML process definitions; no legacy stage orchestrator.

## Packages

- `internal/domain/definition` — Process Design (model, validation, conditions)
- `internal/domain/runtime` — Process Runtime entities
- `internal/domain/ports` — `ProcessRepository` persistence port
- `internal/engine` — application layer; `engine.Store` aliases `ports.ProcessRepository`
- `internal/bpmn` — deprecated compat shim (`compat.go` only)
- `internal/bpmnxml` — BPMN 2.0 XML import/export
- `internal/plugin` — integration extensions (assignee/trigger/task/control streams)
- `internal/api` — Chi HTTP; errors `{ error, code }`
- `internal/store/open.go` — `STORE_BACKEND`: `db` | `file` | `memory`

## Invariants

- `userTask`: multi-sign modes `any|all|sequential` (或签/会签/顺签); complete requires `assignee` when multiple assignees
- Deploy bumps version; instances pin snapshot at start
- New store methods → implement in `memory`, `gormstore`, `filestore`
- Advanced BPMN (boundary events, complex/event gateways, pools/lanes, call activity, etc.) → extension-backed per [docs/ddd/extensions.md](../../docs/ddd/extensions.md); domain IR first, plugins for execution

## TDD

Layer-mapped test workflow: [docs/ddd/testing.md](../../docs/ddd/testing.md). Cursor rule: [ddd-tdd.mdc](./ddd-tdd.mdc).

- Domain (`definition`, `runtime`): pure table-driven tests, no I/O
- Ports: `RunProcessRepositoryContract` in `internal/domain/ports/testing`
- Engine: `memory.NewStore()` integration tests
- HTTP: `internal/api` only

